<div id="container">
<h3></h3>
<div class='layout'><p>4 Library</p><p>第4章 图书馆</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>VENABILI, DORS:……Historian, born in Cinna…………life might well have continued on……uneventful course were it……for……fact that, after……had spent……years on……faculty of Streeling University,……became involved with……young Hari Seldon during……Flight……</p><p>铎丝·凡纳比里：……历史学家，生于锡纳……若非她在斯璀璘大学担任教职两年后，邂逅了处于“逃亡期”的青年哈里·谢顿，她很可能继续过着平静无波的日子……</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>ENCYCLOPEDIA GALACTICA</p><p>……《银河百科全书》</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The room that Hari Seldon found himself in……larger than Hummins room in……Imperial Sector. It……a bedroom with……corner serving as a washroom……with no sign of……cooking or dining facilities. There……no window, though……in……ceiling……a grilled ventilator that made a steady sighing noise. </p><p>哈里·谢顿如今置身的房间，比夫铭在皇区的住所来得宽敞。它是一间套房，其中一角充作盥洗间，却不见任何烹饪或进餐设备。四面都没有窗户，不过天花板上有个罩着网格的抽风机，不断发出稳定的轻微噪音。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon looked about a……ruefully.</p><p>谢顿带着些许失望，四处张望了一下。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Hummin interpreted that look with……usual assured manner……said, "Its only……tonight, Seldon. Tomorrow morning someone will come to install……at……University……you will be more comfortable."</p><p>夫铭以惯有的自信猜到了谢顿的心事，他说：“谢顿，只是今晚暂住而已。明天早上会有人来，把你安置到大学里，你就会比较舒服了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Pardon……Hummin,……how do……know that?"</p><p>“对不起，夫铭，可是你又怎么知道？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I will make arrangements. I know……or……people here"--he smiled briefly without humor--"and I have a favor or……I……ask repayment for.……lets go into some details."</p><p>“我会做好安排，我在这里认识一两个人。”他露出一丝冷笑，“我帮助过他们，可以请他们还我一两个人情。现在，我们来谈谈细节。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He gazed steadily at Seldon……said, "Whatever……have left in your hotel room is lost. Does that include anything irreplaceable?"</p><p>他定睛凝视着谢顿，又说：“你留在旅馆房间的行李等于通通丢了。里面有没有任何无法弥补的东西？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Nothing really irreplaceable. I have some personal items I value……their association with my past life,……if they……gone, they……gone. There are, of course, some notes on my paper. Some calculations.……paper itself."</p><p>“没有什么真正无法弥补的。有些私人物品我很珍惜，因为具有纪念价值，不过丢了就丢了吧。此外，当然还有些和论文有关的笔记、一些计算稿，以及那篇论文。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Which is……public knowledge until such time as it is removed from circulation as dangerous--which it probably will……Still,……be able to……my hands on a copy, Im sure. In……case,……can reconstruct……cant you?"</p><p>“那篇论文如今是公开的资料，哪天它被视为危险的邪说，才会禁止流传……这是可能发生的事。话说回来，我总有办法弄到一份副本，这点我绝对肯定。无论如何，你都能重新推导一遍，对不对？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I can. Thats……I said there……nothing really irreplaceable. Also,……lost nearly a thousand credits, some books, clothing, my tickets back to Helicon, things like that."</p><p>“对，所以我说没有什么真正无法弥补的。此外，我还丢了将近一千信用点、一些书籍和衣物，以及回赫利肯的旅票，诸如此类的东西。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"All replaceable.--Now I will arrange……you to have a credit tile in my name, charged to……That will take care of ordinary expenses."</p><p>“全都不成问题。我会用我的名义帮你申请一张信用瓷卡，记到我的账上。这样就能应付你的一般开销。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Thats unusually generous of you. I cant accept it."</p><p>“你实在慷慨得过分，我不能接受。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Its……generous at all, since Im hoping to save……Empire in that fashion.……must accept it."</p><p>“一点也不算慷慨，因为我这样做是希望能拯救帝国。你无论如何都要接受。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But……much……you afford, Hummin?……be using……at best, with an uneasy conscience."</p><p>“可是你付得起多少呢，夫铭？即使我勉强接受，也会良心不安。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Whatever……need……survival or reasonable comfort I……afford, Seldon. Naturally, I wouldnt want……to……to……the University gymnasium or hand……a million credits in largess."</p><p>“谢顿，你的基本衣食住行，以及任何合理的享乐，我全都负担得起。自然，我不会希望你试图买下大学体育馆，或是慷慨地捐出一百万信用点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You neednt worry,……with my name on record--"</p><p>“你不用担心，可是让我的名字留下记录……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It might as well……It is absolutely forbidden……the Imperial government to exercise……security control over……University or……members. There is complete freedom. Anything……be discussed here, anything……be said here."</p><p>“这没有关系，帝国政府绝不能对这所大学或其成员采取任何安全控制。这里有百分之百的自由，任何事都能谈论，什么话都可以说。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What about violent crime?"</p><p>“万一有暴力犯罪呢？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Then……University authorities themselves handle……with reason……care--and there……virtually no crimes of violence.……students……faculty appreciate their freedom……understand……terms.……much rowdiness,……beginning of riot……bloodshed,……the government……feel it……a right to break……unwritten agreement……send in……troops. No……wants that,……even……government, so a delicate balance is maintained. In other words, Demerzel himself……not have……plucked……of……University without a great deal more cause than anyone in……University……given……government in at least a century……a half. On……other hand, if……are lured……the grounds by a student-agent--"</p><p>“那么校方会以合理而谨慎的方式出面处理……其实几乎没有什么暴力犯罪。学生和教员都珍惜他们拥有的自由，并且了解它的分寸。过度的喧闹是暴动和流血的开端，政府可能就会觉得有权打破不成文约定，而派军队进入校园。没有人愿意发生这种事，甚至政府也不愿意，因而维持着一种微妙的平衡。换句话说，丹莫刺尔本人也不能把你从这所大学抓走，除非大学里出现了至少一个半世纪以来从未有过的严重事端。反之，假如你被特工学生诱出校园……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Are there student-agents?"</p><p>“有特工学生吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"How……I say? There……be.……ordinary individual……be threatened or maneuvered or simply bought--and……remain thereafter in……service of Demerzel or of someone else,……that matter. So I must emphasize this:……are safe in……reasonable sense,……no……is absolutely safe.……will have to be careful.……though I give……that warning, I don't want……to cower through life. On……whole,……will be……more secure here than……would have been if……had returned to Helicon or gone to……world of……Galaxy outside Trantor."</p><p>“我怎么说得准？或许有吧。总之，任何一个普通人都能被威胁、被设计，或是直接被收买，从此就一直为丹莫刺尔或其他人服务。所以我必须强调一点：理论上你无论如何都很安全，可是没有任何人是绝对安全的，你必须自己多加小心。不过，虽然我给你这样的警告，我却不希望你的日子过得畏畏缩缩。整体而言，比起回到赫利肯或是跑到川陀以外的任何世界，你待在这里要安全得多。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I hope so," said Seldon drearily.</p><p>“我希望果真如此。”谢顿闷闷不乐地说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I know so," said Hummin,……I would……feel it wise to leave you."</p><p>“我知道的确如此，”夫铭说，“否则我会感到离开你是不智之举。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Leave me?" Seldon looked up sharply. "You cant do that.……know this world. I dont."</p><p>“离开我？”谢顿猛然抬起头来，“你不能这么做。你了解这个世界，我却不然。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You will be with others……know this world,……know this part of……in fact, even better than I……As……myself, I must……I have been with……all this……and I dare……abandon my……life……longer. I must……attract……much attention to myself. Remember that I have my……insecurities, just as……have yours."</p><p>“你将和其他了解这个世界的人在一起，事实上，他们对此地的了解甚至在我之上。至于我自己，我必须走了。我已经跟你在一起整整一天，我不敢继续不顾自己的生活。我自己绝不能吸引太多的注意。你应该记得，我和你一样有安全上的顾虑。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon blushed. "Youre right. I cant expect……to endanger yourself indefinitely on my behalf. I hope……are……already ruined."</p><p>谢顿不禁面红耳赤。“你说得对。我不能期望你不断为我赴汤蹈火，希望现在还没有毁了你。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Hummin said coolly, "Who……tell? We live in dangerous times. Just remember that if anyone……make……times safe--if……for ourselves, then……those……follow after us--it is you.……that thought be your driving force, Seldon."</p><p>夫铭以冷淡的语调说：“谁知道呢？我们生在一个险恶的时代。你只要记住一件事，若说有什么人能创造安全的时代……即使不为我们，也要为我们的后代……那个人就是你。谢顿，让这个想法成为你的原动力。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Sleep eluded Seldon. He tossed……turned in……dark, thinking. He……have never felt quite so alone or quite so helpless as he……after Hummin……nodded, pressed……hand briefly,……left……behind.……he……on a strange world--and in a strange part of that world. He……without……only person he could consider a friend (and that of less than a days duration)……he……no idea of where he……going or what he would be doing, either tomorrow or at……time in……future.</p><p>今晚睡眠与谢顿无缘。他在黑暗中辗转反侧，思绪一直停不下来。在夫铭点了点头，轻轻握了握他的手，然后离他而去之后，谢顿感受到前所未有的孤独、前所未有的无助。如今他置身一个陌生的世界，而且是这个世界的一个陌生角落。连唯一可以当做朋友的人（却也不到一天的交情）都不在身边，而且他对自己何去何从毫无概念，不论是明天或是未来任何时刻。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>None of that……conducive to sleep……of course, at about……time he decided, hopelessly, that he would……sleep that night……possibly, ever again, exhaustion overtook him……</p><p>当然，这些想法全都无助于入眠。差不多在他绝望地认定今晚将失眠到天亮，而这种情况今后还有可能发生之际，极度的困倦终于将他席卷……</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>When he woke up it……still dark--or……quite,……across……room he……a……light flashing brightly……rapidly, accompanied by a harsh, intermittent buzz. Undoubtedly, it……that which……awakened him. </p><p>当他醒来的时候，屋内依旧一片黑暗……也并非全然如此，因为在房间另一侧，他看见一道明亮的红光在迅速闪动，伴随着一阵刺耳的、断断续续的嗡嗡声。毫无疑问，将他吵醒的就是这个声音。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>As he tried to remember where he……and to make some sort of sense……of……limited messages……senses were receiving,……flashing……buzzing ceased……he became aware of a peremptory rapping.</p><p>当他正在努力回忆身在何处，并试图从感官所接收的有限讯息理出一个头绪时，闪光与嗡嗡声突然停止。接着，他听到一阵凶猛的敲击声。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Presumably,……rapping……at……door,……he didnt remember where……door was. Presumably, also, there……a contact that would flood……room with light,……he didnt remember where that……either.</p><p>敲击声想必源自房门，他却不记得房门的位置。此外，想必有个开关能让室内大放光明，可是他也忘了开关在哪里。</p></div>
